#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:31
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:33
msgid ""
"PyVista is the foundational Python library for 3D visualization and mesh "
"analysis in scientific computing and engineering. PyVista plays the same "
"role for 3D data that pandas plays for tabular data and xarray plays for "
"labeled n-dimensional arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:38
msgid "a NumPy-native API for 3D visualization and mesh analysis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:39
msgid "dataset structures and filters for points, surfaces, and volumes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:40
msgid "one plotting framework for notebooks, scripts, CI, and apps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:41
msgid "streamlined 3D for newcomers and graphics experts alike"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:43
msgid ""
"Use PyVista for figures in papers and presentations, interactive analysis in"
" notebooks, and as the visualization layer of larger Python tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:48
msgid "Built for production"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:50
msgid ""
"3D code has to keep working when the underlying graphics stack changes. "
"PyVista is image-regression tested on every commit across the supported "
"matrix of Python and `VTK`_ releases. Public APIs follow a deliberate "
"deprecation lifecycle (warn, then error, then remove) across at least three "
"minor versions, and every release ships wheels for every supported Python "
"version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:57
msgid ""
"The C++ toolkit underneath does not provide the same guarantees. Its Python "
"bindings shift between releases, large parts of the surface ship without "
"test coverage, and rendering changes are not gated on visual diffs. PyVista "
"is what science and engineering teams reach for when code written today has "
"to still produce the same picture two years from now."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:65
msgid "Built to extend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:67
msgid ""
"Downstream libraries build on PyVista through a small, lazily evaluated "
"extension API. Third-party packages attach domain-specific filters and "
"plotter components via registered accessors, with no subclassing, no monkey-"
"patching, and no vendoring of upstream algorithms. This is the same contract"
" pandas exposes for tabular accessors and xarray exposes for labeled arrays."
" See :ref:`extending-pyvista` for the full contract."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:74
msgid ""
"For a curated, continuously updated list of domain-specific tooling that "
"interoperates with or is built on PyVista, see `awesome-pyvista "
"<https://github.com/pyvista/awesome-pyvista>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/index.rst:78
msgid ""
"Reach for the underlying `VTK`_ toolkit directly only when there is "
"genuinely no PyVista equivalent. When that happens, please file an issue. "
"There should be one."
msgstr ""

